    <tax:treatment obkms_id="50e0a84e-1b39-4577-8e87-bbd7af99fd31" obkms_process="TRUE">
      <tax:nomenclature obkms_id="94687dd0-14c4-4fb9-9e32-95339fcae249" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:name obkms_id="2ea59314-d14c-42f8-a26d-44fcbe84cc7c" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name>
        <tax:status>gen. nov.</tax:status>
      </tax:nomenclature>
      <tax:div type="materials_examined" obkms_id="6042381d-4d0b-41b1-a750-a7eba5e23b2c" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:p>Type species:<tax:name obkms_id="f0411219-a908-4bb4-9a34-9b58b15d57d1" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pseudachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>romeroi</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank><dwc:scientificNameAuthorship>Simon 1986: 300</dwc:scientificNameAuthorship></tax:xmldata>Pseudachorutes romeroiSimón 1986: 300</tax:name>
</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="diagnosis" obkms_id="0a39f3eb-f132-428d-9cd0-0d6bd058d279" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:p>Diagnosis. Habitus of<tax:name obkms_id="9ba95d94-69b9-43f6-8df4-7665777e3284" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pseudachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pseudachorutes</tax:name> -type. Small size. Pigmentation bluish-grey. Ocelli 8 + 8, postantennal organ oval. Buccal cone very long, mandibles absent, maxilla styliform. Labrum long pointed at apex. Labium without organites x and papillate setae L. Head with unpaired seta d1 present and seta a0 absent. Tibiotarsal chaetotaxy reduced. Furcula present.</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="etymology">
        <tax:p>Etymology. Dedicated to José Carlos Simón Benito, a prominent Spanish researcher of collembolan fauna, who described thetype species of the new genus.</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="discussion" obkms_id="df83c1f3-f786-4e11-811c-4406a839bc31" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:p>Remarks.<tax:name obkms_id="620784e0-e892-4ba0-b8c8-00d38e9a54a2" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name> gen. nov. is most similar to<tax:name obkms_id="923cfaa3-e4a2-4bb2-a10c-76f3b2cd8c4e" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pseudachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pseudachorutes</tax:name> in the presence of full number of ocelli, postantennal organ and furcula. Nevertheless it can be easily distinguished from this genus by the absence of mandibles (vs. mandibles present), very long buccal cone (vs. short or prolonged) and 15–17, 15–17, 14–16 setae on tibiotarsi I, II and III (vs. 19, 19, 18 or 18, 18, 17).<tax:name obkms_id="ffe72dd2-6acd-42c1-bf1f-ffae6c718a9d" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name> gen. nov. shares withParanurida and<tax:name obkms_id="bbbc4146-131f-4631-a0b0-062be794a89b" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pongeia</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pongeia</tax:name> lack of mandibles. However, they differ in many essential characters e.g. the number of ocelli (<tax:name obkms_id="2c2a6cb6-b63f-4409-b763-9cf0bbec1b7c" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name> gen. nov. 8 + 8,Paranurida 2 + 2,<tax:name obkms_id="946e88b8-4717-4ad6-800a-c8045f8ac9dc" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pongeia</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pongeia</tax:name> eyes absent), the presence of postantennal organ (<tax:name obkms_id="cc46723e-2fc0-48cd-a14c-c8f94425f97c" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name> gen. nov. and<tax:name obkms_id="60b11a37-764f-445a-b5c2-a5911bdbdf6c" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pongeia</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pongeia</tax:name> present,Paranurida absent), the shape of buccal cone (<tax:name obkms_id="e3ffdb37-7ff7-440b-81df-4a6d75fc7ae1" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name> gen. nov. very long,Paranurida and<tax:name obkms_id="43ed53bd-61ed-427c-bf22-06e840ef90fd" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pongeia</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pongeia</tax:name> slightly elongated), the shape of maxillar head (<tax:name obkms_id="6c9bc212-6a0e-4db7-9a98-77a95d8b263e" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name> gen. nov. andParanurida styliform,<tax:name obkms_id="75d88ed2-8e70-46d7-9c55-b7608706a692" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pongeia</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pongeia</tax:name> globular) and the presence of furcula (<tax:name obkms_id="6b867a70-0d56-4221-bfb2-389ff006f251" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Simonachorutes</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Simonachorutes</tax:name> gen. nov. present,Paranurida and<tax:name obkms_id="59a0ed42-a7cd-45ab-b628-2e04a62a55c1" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Entognatha</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Collembola</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Neanuridae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Pongeia</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Pongeia</tax:name> absent).</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
    </tax:treatment>
